    "description": "5-5-22 City Council Meeting Agenda: https://www.brisbaneca.org/citycouncil/page/city-council-meeting-90<br /><br />Members of the public may join the Regular City Council Meeting by using the following Zoom Webinar information: <br /><br />Join Zoom Webinar (please use the latest version: www.zoom.us/download):<br />https://www.brisbaneca.org/cc-zoom<br />Webinar ID: 991 9362 8666<br />Passcode: 123456<br />Call In Number:  1 (669) 900-9128<br /><br />SPECIAL ASSISTANCE<br />If you need special assistance to participate in this meeting, please contact the City Clerk at (415) 508-2113.  Notification in advance of the meeting will enable the City to make reasonable arrangements to ensure accessibility to this meeting.<br /><br />00:00:00 PREAMBLE<br />00:02:33 CALL TO ORDER, PLEDGE OF ALLEGIANCE<br />00:02:55 ROLL CALL<br />00:03:45 ADOPTION OF AGENDA<br /><br />AWARDS AND PRESENTATIONS<br />00:04:10 A. Proclaiming May 15-21, 2022 as National Public Works Week<br />00:12:57 B. Proclaiming May 15-21, 2022 as Emergency Medical Services Week<br />00:16:28 C. Proclaiming May 2022 as Wildfire Preparedness Month<br /><br />00:19:21 ORAL COMMUNICATIONS NO. 1<br /><br />00:19:53 CONSENT CALENDAR<br />D. Approve Minutes of City Council Meeting of April 7, 2022<br />E. Approve Minutes of City Council Closed Session Meeting of April 7, 2022<br />F. Approve Minutes of City Council Meeting of April 21, 2022<br />G. Approve Minutes of City Council Closed Session Meeting of April 21, 2022<br />H. Adoption of a Resolution Declaring the Continued Need to Conduct City Council, Commission and Committee Meetings Remotely Due to Health and Safety Concerns for the Public<br /><br />00:22:10 PUBLIC HEARING<br />   I. Consider Introduction of an Ordinance to amend Brisbane Municipal Code Title 17 (Zoning Ordinance) to achieve consistency with housing-related state legislation <br />(Proposed amendments include: establishing objective design and development standards for housing development projects; allowing multiple family dwellings in the SCRO-1 District by right; and establishing procedures and requirements for an administrative Housing Development Permit for qualifying housing development projects. This Ordinance has been revised to eliminate proposed amendments to the NCRO-2 District.)<br />00:22:52 Staff Report<br />00:29:00 Council Questions/Discussion<br />00:34:15 Public Comment<br /><br />NEW BUSINESS<br />  00:36:50 J. Reject all bids received April 21, 2022 for the 18 Solano Street Retaining Wall Project, Job No. 922B. <br />  00:39:26 K. Receive Solid Waste Collection Rate Adjustment (The Council will receive South San Francisco Scavenger\u2019s 2022 rate increase of 5.19%)<br /><br />STAFF REPORTS<br />  00:44:10 L. City Manager\u2019s Report on upcoming activities<br /><br />MAYOR/COUNCIL MATTERS<br />  00:47:41 M. Countywide Assignments and Subcommittee Reports<br />  01:07:31 N. Written Communications<br /><br />01:08:42 ORAL COMMUNICATIONS NO. 2<br />ADJOURNMENT",
